SMBC Nikko Securities Hires Former Mizuho Analyst Kouichi Niwa

-- B y   M a s a a k i   I w a m o t o   a n d   T o s h i r o   H a s e g a w a
-- 
2011-09-21T08:19:51Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-21/smbc-nikko-securities-hires-former-mizuho-analyst-kouichi-niwa.html
SMBC Nikko Securities Inc., a unit
of  Japan ’s second-biggest bank by market value, hired Kouichi Niwa, a former non-banking financial sector analyst at Mizuho
Securities Co., said Kiyoo Kuniyoshi, a Tokyo-based spokesman
for SMBC Nikko.  Niwa, ranked the fifth-best analyst in Japan for securities
and insurance firms and other financial companies by the Nikkei
Veritas newspaper, covered  Orix Corp. (8591) , Promise Co. and Dai-ichi
Life Insurance Co. at Mizuho Securities, a unit of Japan’s third
biggest bank by market value. He joined Mizuho in 2008 and
previously worked for Kokusai Securities Co.  The number of equity analysts at SMBC Nikko has increased
to 33, Kuniyoshi said in an interview today. Niwa’s hiring means
SMBC Nikko now cover all sectors of the market for the first
time since the equity research division launched in August 2010,
Kuniyoshi said.  To contact the reporters on this story:
